Three Cabinet Secretaries: Mwangi Kiunjuri, Charles Keter and Henry Rotich are on the spot after opposition leaders, Musalia Mudavadi and Moses Wetang’ula called for their removal citing poor performance in their respective dockets. This in the wake of protests over the new maize prices approved by the cabinet this week. Agriculture Cabinet Secretary, Mwangi Kiunjuri is accused of letting down farmers who are staring at a bleak future as Kenyans continue to shoulder the  tax burden. 